<paragraph blockId="111.[189,1399,267,752]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Inner side of LAPs with large, conspicuous, sharply defined, prominent ridge; short oblique central part of ridge; dorsal part widened, strongly vertically elongate, nearly triangular, with pointed (in proximal LAPs extremely elongate) dorsal tip, ventro-proximal tip slightly pointed; ventral portion of central part of ridge very short, ventro-proximally pointing, sharply separated from ventral part of LAP; inner side of distal edge of LAP with two to three small, well-defined, strongly prominent spurs composed of slightly more densely meshed stereom; inner side of tentacle notch relatively small, poorly defined laterally; moderately shallow, dorsally well-defined vertical furrow with small, irregular perforations dorsally bordering tentacle notch.</paragraph>
